TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (72.0, 129.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Manchester, in the heart of the northwest of England, is tonight host ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to a British political first. I'm Alastair Stewart. For the first time on " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'British television, live in front of a representative studio audience, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we'll be hearing from three men, each hoping to be the leader of the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'next UK government in the first election debate.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (141.0, 279.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Good evening, and welcome to the first election debate. Over the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'past 50 years, there have been numerous attempts to get the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'leaders of the three big political parties to debate with each other ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"during an election. Tonight, history in the making, as we're joined by " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the leader of the Liberal Democrats, Nick Clegg, the Conservative ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'party leader, David Cameron, and the leader of the Labour Party, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Gordon Brown. This debate will mainly focus on domestic affairs, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'important issues that affect our everyday lives. If you want to make ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'your own comments and follow the debate online, you can do so by ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"going to ITV.com. In a moment, we'll be taking questions from our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"studio audience, but first, let's hear a brief opening statement from " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"each of the leaders. We'll start with Nick Clegg. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 513.0), (294.0, 443.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I believe the way things are is not the way things have to be. You're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'going to be told tonight by these two that the only choice you can ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"make is between two old parties who've been running things for " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"years. I'm here to persuade you that there is an alternative. I think " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we have a fantastic opportunity to do things differently for once. If ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we do things differently, we can create the fair society, the fair ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'country we all want: a fair tax system, better schools, an economy ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'no longer held hostage by greedy bankers, decent, open politics. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Those are the changes I believe in. I really wouldn't be standing " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"here tonight if I didn't think they were all possible. So don't let " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'anyone tell you that the only choice is old politics. We can do ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"something new; we can do something different this time. That's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"what I'm about; that's what the Liberal Democrats offer.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (455.0, 604.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"These are no ordinary times, and this is no ordinary election. We've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'just been going through the biggest global financial crisis in our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"lives, and we're moving from recession to recovery, and I believe " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we're moving on a road to prosperity for all. Now, every promise you " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'hear from each of us this evening depends on one thing: a strong ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'economy. And this is the defining year. Get the decisions right now, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and we can have secure jobs, we can have standards of living ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'rising, and we can have everybody better off. Get the decisions ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'wrong now, and we could have a double-dip recession. And ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'because we believe in fairness, as we cut the deficit, over these ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'next few years, we will protect your police, your National Health ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Service, and we will protect your schools. I know what this job ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'involves; I look forward to putting my plan to you this evening. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (72.0, 233.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"I think it's great we're having these debates, and I hope they go " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'some way to restore some of the faith and some of the trust into our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'politics, because we badly need that once again in this country. The ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"expenses saga brought great shame on parliament. I'm extremely " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'sorry for everything that happened. Your politicians, frankly all of us, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'let you down. Now, there is a big choice at this election: we can go ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'on as we are, or we can say no, Britain can do much better; we can ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'deal with our debts, we can get our economy growing and avoid this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'jobs tax, and we can build a bigger society. But we can only do this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'if we recognise we need join together, we need to come together, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we need to recognise we're all in this together. Now, not everything " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Labour has done in the last 13 years has been wrong - they've done " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'some good things and I would keep those, but we need change, and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"it's that change I want to help to lead. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (251.0, 273.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gentlemen, thank you very much indeed. Our first question is from ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Gerard Oliver who is a retired toxicologist from Cheshire. Mr Oliver.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 507.0), (285.0, 308.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u'Good evening. What key elements for a fair, workable immigration ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'policy need to be put in place to actually make it work effectively?  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 285.0), (320.0, 331.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 513.0), (354.0, 538.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"You know, I've heard the concerns around the country. I've been " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'listening to people. I know people feel there are pressures because ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"of immigration. That's why we want to control and manage " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'immigration. And I when I became Prime Minister, I did a number of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'things. First, I introduced a points system so no unskilled worker ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'from outside the European Union can come to Britain now. I also ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'said that jobs had to be advertised in Jobcentres where there were ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'skills that there were shortages of that we needed people in this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"country. I then said we're going to look at all the range of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'occupations where people come from abroad. I talked to a chef the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"other day who was training. I said in future, when we do it, there'll " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'be no chefs allowed in from outside the European Union. Then I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'talked to some care assistants - no care assistants come in from ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'outside the European Union. We are a tolerant, we are a diverse ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"country, but the controls on migration that I'm introducing and I will " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'see go further are the right controls, the right policy for Britain. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 290.0), (550.0, 561.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'David Cameron.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (584.0, 768.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Gerard, what I would say is that immigration is simply too high at the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'moment. It has been these last ten years, and it does need to come ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"down. I think the pressures that we've put on housing and health " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and education have been too great. If you look at the...what's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'happening with immigration, the difference between the amount of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"people going to live overseas and those coming here, it's been often " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"as high as 200,000. That's equivalent to two million across a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"decade. It's too much. I want us to bring immigration down so it is in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the tens of thousands, not the hundreds of thousands. How would ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we do that? I think we need to have not just a points system, but ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'also a limit on migration when people are coming from outside the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'European Union for economic reasons. I also think when new ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'countries join the European Union, that actually we should have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"transitional controls so they can't all come here at once. It's been " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'too high these last few years, and I would dearly love to get it down ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to the levels it was in the past so it is no longer an issue in our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 349.0), (72.0, 83.0)) {}
  [
    u"politics as it wasn't in the past. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 269.0), (95.0, 106.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Nick Clegg.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (130.0, 336.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"Gerard, you talked about a fair, workable immigration system. That's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"exactly what I want. What's happened over the last several years is " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'almost precisely the reverse. You have had lots and lots of tough ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'talking about immigration from both Conservative and Labour ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'governments, and complete chaos in the actual administration of the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'system. It was a Conservative government that removed the exit ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'controls so we knew who was leaving as well as who was coming ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"in. It's what the Labour government followed up on as well. What I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'think we need to do is, firstly, make sure we restore those exit ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'controls, so we have borders so we know exactly who is coming in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'but also when they are supposed to leave. The second thing I would ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'do is this. At the moment under the immigration system, if you want ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to come and work in this country, you have to show two things: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300}
  ]
  [
    u"firstly, that you've got a sponsor who is sponsoring your arrival in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'this country, and secondly, that there is a job for you to do. I want to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'add a third element: that you also only go to a place, to a region, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'where you are needed. So that we only send immigrants to those ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'places where they can be coped.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 497.0), (348.0, 382.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"You've heard what each has had to say on immigration. It's now " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"your chance to contest the others' arguments. And you, Gordon " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Brown, will start.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 514.0), (394.0, 589.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"Let's be honest with each other, net inward migration is falling. It's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"fallen three years ago, two years ago, and it's falling this year. It's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'falling as a result of the action we are taking and will continue to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'take. To stop illegal migration, which is what Nick has referred to, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"border controls have been brought in and we're counting people out " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and in from the end of this year. It was a policy the Conservatives ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"scrapped before 1997. We've got ID cards now for foreign nationals " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"so an employer can see whether they're legal or illegal. So we're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"taking precise and specific action. What I wouldn't do is have an " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"arbitrary cap. An arbitrary cap means an employer... And I've been " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'visiting a lot of employers in this region, who wants to bring ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'someone in from abroad, needs that skilled worker, the skill is not ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'here, cannot do that. Net inward migration will continue to fall under ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'our policies. 40,000 less students, I suspect, this year, because of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'our tightening of visa controls. Now, these are the things practically ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we can do. We're a tolerant country but we want proper control over " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'migration. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 287.0), (601.0, 612.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'David Cameron. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 512.0), (636.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"I think a cap is necessary because we're not going to control " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'immigration unless we actually take some quite positive and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"concrete steps. I think we let down everyone if we don't do this " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'properly. I was in Plymouth recently, and a 40-year-old black man ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'made the point to me. He said, "I came here when I was six, I\'ve ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"served in the Royal Navy for 30 years. I'm incredibly proud of my " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"country. But I'm so ashamed that we've had this out-of-control " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'system with people abusing it so badly." If we don\'t address ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"immigration properly, we're letting down immigrant communities, as " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'well as everybody else. So we do need a cap. As well as border ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'controls that Gordon talks about, and I support strong border ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 504.0), (72.0, 129.0)) {}
  [
    u'controls, I think we need to go one step further and have a proper ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'border police force so we combine at our borders, customs, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'immigration, security, and police, so we make the most of the fact ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that we do have policeable borders, and we can stop more illegal ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'immigration that way as well.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (141.0, 336.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'The truth is that there is good immigration and there is bad ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'immigration. I was in a hospital, a paediatric hospital in Cardiff a few ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'months ago, treating very sick premature young babies. I was being ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'shown around and there were a large number of babies needing to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'be treated. There was a ward standing completely empty, though it ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'had the latest equipment. I said to the ward sister "What\'s going on? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Why are there no babies being treated?" She said "New rules mean ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we can't employ any doctors from outside the European Union with " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the skills needed". That\'s an example of where the rules are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'stopping good immigration which actually helps our public services ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to work properly. That's where I want to see, not an arbitrary cap. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"We can't just say a cap, what is it? 10, 10,000? A million? What if " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'you reach the cap in the middle of summer and someone wants to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'come and play football for Manchester United or Manchester City? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Do you say they can't come? No, let's have a regional approach " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'where you only make sure the immigrants who come go to those ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'regions where they can be supported.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 508.0), (348.0, 405.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"On Nick's point, of course we've benefited from immigration for " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'decades in our country. People have come here to work hard, to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'make a contribution, to bring their special skills. We see that in our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"health service and schools all the time. But I do think it's got out of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'control, and it does need to be brought back under control. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (417.0, 555.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"I don't like these words, because we're bringing it under control. Net " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'inward migration is falling and will continue to fall as a result of the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"measures we've taken. We've brought together the police and the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"immigration officials and the customs officials in one agency. We're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"doing that already. Illegal immigrants are deterred because we've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'got ID cards for foreign nationals now, so an employer cannot say to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'someone "You can come and have this job". They\'ve got to ask for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the identity card first. There are big fines if employers break the law. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Now, we've got to do more. That means we've got to tighten the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"number of skills we need in this country. That's why we're moving " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'from care assistants to chefs right through other occupations where ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we train up British people to do the skills. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 506.0), (567.0, 635.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"A lot of people would ask, though, we've had 13 years of a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"government that's now only started to talk about addressing this " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'issue. If you look at the numbers, net migration levels before 1997 ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'were never greater than 77,000 a year. Under your government, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"they've never been less than 140,000 a year. That's a very big " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'number. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 400.0), (647.0, 658.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN:  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'But you accept the figures are now falling. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 514.0), (670.0, 693.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"You're only starting before an election to take the steps that need to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'be taken. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 377.0), (705.0, 716.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"I'm going to bring Nick Clegg in now. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 509.0), (739.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I think this is partly what's been going wrong for so long. We have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'had both major parties running governments over the last 20 years ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 515.0), (72.0, 187.0)) {}
  [
    u'talking tough about immigration and delivering complete chaos in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the way in which it's run. I'm like anybody else. I just want a fair, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'workable immigration system that counts people in, counts people ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"out, only makes sure immigrants come here if there's jobs for them " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to do in parts of the country where they don't place unreasonable " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'strain on housing, public services and so on. I think the regional ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"approach that we're putting forward, which would be a major " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'innovation, they do it in Canada, they do it in Australia, it would be a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'major innovation here, which I think would restore public confidence ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"in an immigration where people feel it's complete chaos. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (199.0, 290.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'You see, I agree with Nick, an arbitrary national cap will not work. I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'think the Conservatives are not even giving the number for that cap. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"They can't tell us what they will do. Take the controls we're putting " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'in, add to the points system, restrict more occupations in future ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'where we can train up people to have the skills. My Britain of vision ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'moving forward is we train the young people up to get the skills for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the future and we will need less people to come in to meet the skills ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"shortages of the past. That's now what we're now doing. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (302.0, 371.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"It's absolutely true that the other side of the coin is proper welfare " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'reform. We have got too many people who could work, who are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"offered work but who don't work. That has actually drawn a lot of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'people into our country. We do need to reform welfare. But again, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"13 years have gone by when welfare hasn't been properly reformed. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Can I just ask Nick one? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 420.0), (383.0, 394.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'There are 2.5 million more jobs in this country. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 512.0), (406.0, 440.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Can I just ask Nick one question about this regional approach? I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"don't quite understand how you can ask people to come to one part " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of the country and rely on them staying in that one country... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 284.0), (452.0, 463.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Oh, very easily. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 432.0), (475.0, 486.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON:  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'You have a vision of the M62 with a border post? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (498.0, 612.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'No, no, no. Very, very easily. They do it in other countries. Basically ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"it means if you're an employer and you're employing someone " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"who's got a work permit, then you will need to make sure that in that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"work permit, they're only able to work in the region where you are " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"offering them work. And if you offer them work when they don't have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"a work permit which says they're entitled to be in that region, then " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you're acting illegally. They do it in other countries, we should do it " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'here. Because the truth is that our country has lots of different ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"needs in different parts of the country. That's not being reflected in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the immigration system in which the public has lost any confidence. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (624.0, 716.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"Gentlemen, I'm going to leave it there because we have a lot of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'questions to get through. You yourselves have said we want to get ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"some questions. Let's go to the audience and take another. Our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'next question is on law and order. I need to point out that it is an ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'area where powers are devolved to the parliament in Scotland and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'from this week, also the assembly in Northern Ireland. This question ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'comes from optician and mother of two, Jacqueline Salmon. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Jacqueline, your question. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (728.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u'Good evening. I was born and still work in Burnley, Lancashire. The ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'town has the highest burglary rate per head of population in the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'entire country. What confidence can you give me that towns such as ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 494.0), (72.0, 83.0)) {}
  [
    u'this all over the UK can be made safer places to live and work? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (95.0, 279.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"Jacqueline, the system isn't working properly now, there's no doubt " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"about it. We're not seeing enough police on the streets, we're not " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"catching enough burglars, we're not convicting enough. Then we do, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"when we do convict them, they're not getting long enough " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'sentences. I went to Crosby the other day and I was talking to a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'woman there who had been burgled by someone who had just left ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'prison. He stole everything in her house. As he left, he set fire to the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'sofa and her son died from the fumes. That burglar, that murderer, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'could be out of prison in just four-and-a-half years. The system ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"doesn't work, but that sort of sentence is, I think, just completely " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'unacceptable in terms of what the public expect for proper ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"punishment. What have we got to do? We've got to get rid of the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"paperwork and the bureaucracy and we've got to get the police out " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'on the streets. We need very clear signals from our criminal justice ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"system: if you cross someone's threshold and rob their home, you " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'go to prison, and you go to prison for a long time. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 266.0), (302.0, 313.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Nick Clegg. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (337.0, 509.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Jacqueline, you asked, what can we do to stop burglary happening ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'over and over and over and over again. Two things: firstly, quite ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'simply, more police on our streets. This government wants to waste ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'billions of your money on an ID card system so you have to pay for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the privilege of having lots of your own details on a piece of plastic ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'card that you carry around. For pretty well exactly the amount of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'money, your money, that the government is pouring into that, we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'could put 3,000 more police officers on the streets. That is the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'absolute priority for me. The second thing is this: there are too many ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'young offenders who start first getting into trouble with low-level ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'nuisance anti-social behaviour who become the hardened criminals ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"of tomorrow. What we've got to do is stop the young offenders of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'today becoming the hardened criminals tomorrow. In my city of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Sheffield, where I'm an MP, we've done some great things to do " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"exactly that. That's the way to get burglary and crime down. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (521.0, 716.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Jacqueline, as long as anybody feels unsafe, and as long as ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'anybody feels insecure, even although crime is falling - official crime ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"figures show it's falling, and violent crime is falling - I feel that we " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"have got to do far more. And that's why there's three things I want to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"suggest this evening that will make people safer. One is we've got " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to have effective policing on the streets. Police have got to spend ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"80% of their time now on the streets. We've got record police " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'numbers in this country, and we want to maintain that level of police ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'force over the next few years. The second thing is, parents have got ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to accept responsibility for their children. If an order is passed ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'against a teenager, then the parent has also got to accept ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"responsibility, and we're bringing that in now. The third thing I would " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'say is this: if you are dissatisfied with the way the police are treating ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'or the police are dealing with your case, and you are persistently ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"denied the rights you have, then we'll give you the right to take an " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'injunction against the police so you can be sure that your rights ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'against anti-social behaviour and crime are upheld. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 513.0), (728.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'I think one additional point that I would make is if you look at where ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'so much of the burglary, so much of the car crime is coming from, it ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'is actually coming from people who are addicted to drugs. I think ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 514.0), (72.0, 175.0)) {}
  [
    u"we've got to be much faster at getting drug addicts off the streets " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and into treatment. And all too often, that doesn't happen. And even " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"when it does today, they get put on a substitute drug. We're not " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'really dealing with the problem, which is to get these people to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'confront their problems and lead drug-free lives. I even went to a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'drug rehab recently in my own constituency, and met a young man ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'who told me that he committed a certain amount of crimes so he ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'could get in front of a judge who could then get him a place in a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'residential rehab centre. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 513.0), (187.0, 221.0)) {}
  [
    u'We must be mad as a country not to get people into that residential ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'rehab to get them to clean up their lives, so we cut the crime on our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'own streets. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (233.0, 440.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I think, as I say, it's how do we make sure the youngsters of today " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"don't become the hardened criminals of tomorrow? It's that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'conveyor-belt from nuisance at the beginning, anti-social behaviour ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'in our communities, yobs on on the street corner who then become ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the hardened criminals of tomorrow. I think what makes me so ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"angry is that again, it's like the immigration debate: so much tough " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'talk from different governments of different parties for so long has ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'turned our prisons into overcrowded colleges of crime. Do you know ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that young men going into prison now on short-term prison ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'sentences now come out, and nine out of ten of them reoffend, so ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we are reproducing more crime than actually cutting it. What I've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'seen in my city of Sheffield is that you get these youngsters not ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"when they've done serious crimes, but when they're first starting to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"get into trouble, to face their victims, explain why they've done what " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"they've done to their victims, apologise for what they've done, make " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"up for what they've done in the community, cleaning up parks and " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'streets. It has a dramatic effect on their behaviour. I want to change ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"people's behaviour before they become the criminals of tomorrow. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (452.0, 647.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'When I was young, my father ran a youth club with my brother for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'young people, and the more people who do voluntary service and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'give their time in the community to getting young people off the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
