TextArea((95.0, 514.0), (187.0, 371.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'I want to see our education improve as it has done over the last few ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'years. We need teachers with better qualifications. We need young ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'people with the aspiration to succeed, and we need to give people ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the chance to start education early, that's why nursery education " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"starts at three and be able to go through to 18. That's what we are " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'saying in our manifesto, education will be part-time or full-time till ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the age of 18. As far as grades and standards are concerned, I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"myself believe in the highest of standards. I believe if we don't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'search for the highest of standards, then we will not in the end get ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the best pupils coming out of our schools. Yes, we've got to look at " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the different types of exams and we will do so. But I think it's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"important to realise we're in this new world where we are competing " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'with Asia, as well as America and Europe and our young people ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'have got to have the grades, the qualifications to be able to meet ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the best in the world. That's what I want to achieve and I hope I can " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'work with you to do so. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 514.0), (383.0, 578.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'I have every sympathy with what you say because education is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"important, that, as well as getting good grades that actually we're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"opening young people's minds to all the best things that have been " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'written and all the best things that have been said and to really ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'excite people about education. I think there is a danger that our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'education system has become terribly bureaucratic. We send 4,000 ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'pages of information to schools every year. We spend \xa3300 million ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"on educational quangos. We're not getting enough to the frontline, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'following the child into the school. As someone who has got two ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'children, one of whom started at a state school in London, and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"hopefully another child to come, I'm passionate about getting as " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'much money into the school as possible, rather than wasting it in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Whitehall. In terms of exams, we've got to have good external " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"marking, done properly, and high standards. I think that's absolutely " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"key. I wouldn't want to see that change. But let's set the schools " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'free, so we trust in the vocation of the teachers who do what they ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"want - they're there because they have a vocation they care about.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (590.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"John, I think everyone will recognise what you're talking about, this " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'feeling that you have to constantly jump through hoops. The ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'symptoms are everywhere. Our National Curriculum is 600 pages. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'The curriculum in Sweden, which has generally got a fairly good ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'education system, is 16 pages. I just read the other day that head ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'teachers now by e-mail over the last year, have received - get this - ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'4,000 pages of instructions from on high from Whitehall. This is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"crazy. We've got to let head teachers teach, we've got to let " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"teachers teach. We've got to reinstil a sense of enthusiasm and " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"creativity in the way that you are taught. That's why we want to do, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the Liberal Democrats, is to put on to the statute book an Education ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Freedom Act which literally bans government from micromanaging ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'what happens every minute of the day with every single test in every ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"classroom in the country. That's what I'd like to see. I think it would " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'make a big difference to you and other people who are at school. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (85.0, 234.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"But every school has got to be a good school. We've got to insist on " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the highest standards for every school. Since 1997, 1,600 ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'underperforming secondary schools in 1997 went down to 250. Next ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"year, down to zero, as a result of the fact that we're allowing " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'federations, academies, to take over underperforming schools. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"That's the way forward, to insist on the highest standards, to make " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'sure an underperforming school is taken over, to make sure we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'invest enough in the education system to ensure our children are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"properly taught. What I'd be very worried about is if in this difficult " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and straitened time, we were to cut our budgets for education at this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'point in time. I think that would put our children at risk for the future, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and it's very important that we continue to invest in the education of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'every child in this country. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (246.0, 430.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"What I'd say in terms of what I care about most in education with my " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'own children going through the system, I want what every parent in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"this country wants, and it starts with something that actually doesn't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'necessarily cost money, and that is good discipline in our schools. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'In a typical year now, you get 17,000 teachers being attacked by ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"students. We've got a real problem here. There was a case in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Manchester once where a child produced a knife in a school, got ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'excluded, and then the appeals panel put that child back into the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"school. Imagine what that does to the head teacher that's trying to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'keep order. So we say head teachers should be able to exclude ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'difficult pupils and not be overruled by appeals panels. We say ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you've got to change the rules so teachers can keep order in class. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Right now, we seem to be treating the teacher like children and the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"children like the adults. We've got it topsy-turvy, the wrong way " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'round, and we really need to change that so that we have proper ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'discipline and order. Then people can learn. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (441.0, 625.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'I think discipline is important, of course. I think creativity, which I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
