  ]
  [
    u"and that's why where a school is failing, it will be taken over by a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'federation or an academy so that it can work, usually a local ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'federation or a local academy. I want the best discipline in our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"schools as well, and I'm tough on what head teachers have got to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"do to ensure there's discipline not just in the school itself, but " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"around the school as well, but we've got to face up to the fact about " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'spending. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (245.0, 313.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Well, Gordon Brown mentioned spending - absolutely, too right. I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"don't think we're really going to get those smaller class sizes, that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'one-to-one tuition that I think Joel agrees is necessary, the catch-up ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"classes, unless we find the money from savings elsewhere. We've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'spelt that out in our manifesto, so we can provide under our plan ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'\xa32.5 billion extra to our schools. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (325.0, 394.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"I'm going to stop you right there, because I know what the questions " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"are and you don't, but the next question continues that debate. Your " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'answers are entirely a matter for you, and your rebuttals as well, but ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'I think you may find that the next question will continue that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"discussion. It's Robert Lewis, a senior manager in healthcare. Mr " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Lewis, your question. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 504.0), (406.0, 428.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u"How certain can you be that your party's policies will deal with the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'budget deficits without damaging economic growth? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 276.0), (440.0, 451.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Mr Cameron? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 513.0), (475.0, 647.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"This is an absolutely vital question, and I'm glad it's been asked, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"because we've got to get this economy moving. We've got to get " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'this economy growing. What we say is save \xa36 billion in the coming ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'current year in order to stop the jobs tax which we think will derail ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the recovery. Because if you put a tax on jobs, that I think is a jobs ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"killer, it is a recovery killer, it's an economy killer. A hundred of the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'leading business people in this country, people who run companies ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"like Sainsbury's, Marks & Spencers and Mothercare have all said " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that the threat to recovery is not cutting out waste as we say, the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"threat to recovery is Labour's proposal for a jobs tax. So I think " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we've got to remove this dark cloud of a deficit over our economy " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and it makes sense to make a start on that now. Make a start this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'year, to avoid the tax next year, and then we can go forward with ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'further plans to remove our deficit and our debt that will hold our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"country back if we're not careful. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (659.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Where are you, Robert? I can hear your voice, but... Ah, there you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'are, right at the back. Sorry. Behind the camera. Now I can see you. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Robert, I think we need to just be open with you, straight with you, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and we've sought to do that. We've specified - I think we're the only " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'party in politics now, in our manifesto, look at the back of our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'manifesto, which says, here are the figures, this is the way that we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'would find cuts and savings of \xa315 million. How would we do that? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'By things like removing tax credits for the top 20% of recipients of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'tax credits, ending the child trust fund, which gives \xa3250 to all 18-' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 516.0), (72.0, 164.0)) {}
  [
    u"year-olds. I'd love to give everybody \xa3250 but I don't think we can " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'afford it right now. Putting a cap of \xa3400 on any pay increases in the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'public sector for the next two years. But also some long-term ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"choices. I'm the only leader here who is saying very clearly I don't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'think we can either justify or afford the like-for-like replacement of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the Cold War nuclear missile system, the Trident missile system, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'over the next 25 years. It will cost you, all of us, \xa3100 billion. We ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"can't afford it. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (176.0, 359.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"We've been through a terrible financial recession - a global financial " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'recession - and every time we have had to make big choices about ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'what we do. To support the economy when there was no private ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'investment happening; to support people who were unemployed so ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we could keep unemployment down; to support mortgages so there ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"were no mortgage repossessions like the 1990s. Now, we're at a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'critical point in our economy now. I will be honest with you, you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'cannot afford to take money out of the economy now because you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'will put jobs at risk, businesses at risk, and you put the whole ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'recovery at risk. \xa36 billion out of the economy means lost jobs, it ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'means lost businesses, it means lost growth. If you take that money ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'out now, I fear for what could happen, and we do not want to have a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'double-dip recession in this country. Take \xa36 billion out and it is the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'equivalent of taking out thousands of jobs in this economy today ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and making a lot of jobs that are safe at the moment unsafe. I would ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'not recommend that at all. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (371.0, 543.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Let me take on, Robert, this argument directly, the idea that if you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'cut waste this year, you endanger the recovery. Just this week, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we've seen two I think pretty hideous waste stories. The first is that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'civil servants have been given credit cards funded by the tax-payer ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to go out and spend that on food, wine and other things, and that's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'cost \xa31 billion. The second story was that managers in the National ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Health Service, many of whom are paid over \xa3250,000, have had a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"7% pay rise. Are we honestly saying that if you didn't have that sort " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of waste, that sort of excess, that our economy would collapse? I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"think it's nonsense. It's like saying that giving up smoking is " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'somehow going to be bad for your health. Giving up waste would be ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'good for our economy, and it would mean that we could stop this tax ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"rise that's coming down the track, that Britain's biggest business " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"leaders all say will cost jobs. Cut the waste, stop the tax. That's the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'right answer. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (555.0, 750.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'These two constantly argue about waste as if we can create...or we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'can fill the black hole in public finances by saving money on paper ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'clips and pot plants in Whitehall. Of course we can get rid of a bit of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"waste. But that isn't the big... That doesn't really address the big " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'questions we need to ask ourselves. I think we need to be clear with ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you, open with you, straight with you. We've tried to do that. We've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"set out \xa315 billion worth of savings. I've listed some of them. We " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'have one specific tax that we want to introduce to help fill the black ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'hole. We would impose a 10% tax on the profits of the banks, these ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'banks who have got us into the trouble in the first place. I think they ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'should pay you back because you, the taxpayer, have bailed them ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'out, and use that money to deal with the black hole in the finances. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Let's not get obsessed about mythical savings and waste, which is " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the oldest trick in the book, to pretend that you can square a circle ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'like that. Or get obsessed about when you deliver these cuts. The ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'crucial thing is, are we going to be open with people, with you, about ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"how we're going to save money in the long-term? " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (72.0, 279.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Just think how difficult it is to save 50,000, 100,000, 200,000, a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'million, and then think of 6,000 million to be saved in the next nine ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'months before the end of the financial year. I fear for our economy if ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"that happens. The only way we've kept our economy moving " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"forward is not because there's been private investment or bank " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"lending, it's because the government has had to step in to make " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"sure there is sufficient growth. We've prevented unemployment " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"going to the levels of America and Europe. I say you've got to keep " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that support now. Every other European country, America, agrees ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'with that. Only the Conservative Party is against keeping that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"support in the economy now. Now, of course we've got to deal with " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'waste, but if you take the waste out, you put more money into the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"economy to make sure the economy can continue to grow. It's the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'only way we can save jobs and businesses in this country now. I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'say to the whole audience here and to the nation: it is important at ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'this moment to take no risk with the recovery. Once again, the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Conservatives are showing they are a risk to the recovery in this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'country. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 266.0), (291.0, 302.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Nick Clegg. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 514.0), (325.0, 486.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"We all know we've got this great black hole in our public finances. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"That's obvious. We all know we're going to have to save money; we " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"all know we're going to have to make cuts. The question at this " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'election is who is trying to be straight with you about the scale of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"those cuts, how long they'll take? As it happens, this is one area " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'where I would like for once to see politicians put people before ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"politics. What I'm suggesting - I don't know whether Gordon Brown " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and David Cameron will take up this invitation - is that regardless of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the outcome of the general election, that we get the Chancellor and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the shadow Chancellors together, the governor of the Bank of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'England, the head of the Financial Services Authority, to come ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"clean with you about how big this structural deficit is. It's estimated " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to be somewhere around \xa370 billion. And straight with you, finally, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'about how long it is going to take to fill that. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 287.0), (498.0, 509.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'David Cameron. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (532.0, 601.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"There's no doubt the country's going to have to come together to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'deal with this really big problem of the deficit. For every \xa34 that we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'spend right now, the government is borrowing one of those pounds. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Nick keeps saying he's being very straight with you. In his manifesto " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"is a promise for a \xa317 billion tax cut. It is a great idea. I'd love to do " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"it but we don't have \xa317 billion for a tax cut. Gordon is saying... " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 360.0), (613.0, 624.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Nick Clegg on that specific point. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (647.0, 716.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"We've spelt out exactly where that money would come from. We " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'would, for instance, stop this grotesque spectacle of this unfair tax ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'system which has been built up under a succession of Labour and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Conservative governments, where right now, a greedy banker in the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'City of London pays a lower rate of tax on their capital gains than ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'their cleaner does on their wages. We have a tax system... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 352.0), (728.0, 739.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown. Gordon Brown. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (72.0, 164.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Back to the question Robert put, that the PCT, the health authority, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'was finding it very difficult because of the situation at the moment. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Take thousands of millions out of the economy now, take \xa36 billion ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'out of the economy now, and think of the risk to jobs and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'businesses. I say to the Conservatives, of course we want efficiency ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'savings and of course we want to deal with waste, but we cannot ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'afford to see private investment so small and then public investment ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'cut at this time and lots of jobs put at risk. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 287.0), (176.0, 187.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'David Cameron. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 355.0), (210.0, 221.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"Please tell us you won't do that. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (233.0, 313.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'\xa36 billion is one out of every \xa3100 the government spends. What ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"small business in this recession, what big business hasn't had to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'make that sort of decision? Many people are making a much bigger ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'decision. Turn it round the other way and think about it like this. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Gordon is effectively saying, "I want to go on wasting money now so ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'I put up your taxes later." Why should we pay our taxes for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'government waste? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (325.0, 417.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"We've got a responsibility for the overall growth rate of the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"economy. We've got to get this economy moving forward. You can't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'do it with private investment alone. The government has got to play ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"its role. Now, next year, we'll make these bigger savings and of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"course we're going to pay for health and for education, and for " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"policing by what we do on National Insurance. But this year, don't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"pull the money out of the economy, don't put good people's jobs and " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'their businesses at risk now. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (429.0, 497.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'But why do you think it is, I would say, that a hundred of the leading ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'business people in this country, people who run some of the biggest ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'businesses like Corus, like Logica, like Mothercare, why do they ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"say, and they couldn't be more clear, the risk to the economy isn't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"cutting waste, the risk to the economy is Labour's proposal of a jobs " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'tax. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 376.0), (509.0, 520.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown on that specific point. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (544.0, 635.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'The risk to the economy is this year, and every country - America, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the rest of Europe, including Britain - is saying, we've got to make " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'sure we invest in the economy this year so that we can have the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"growth we need. Now, pull out the money, and you've proposed it at " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"every point during this recession, pull out the money and you'll have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"less growth, you'll have less jobs, and you'll have less businesses. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"That's the fear. We've got to take an overall responsibility for the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'whole economy. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (647.0, 716.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"All I would say is this argument I think just doesn't address the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'fundamental issue. There are going to be big things over the next ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'few years, and neither will come clean on this with you, that we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"simply can't afford to do. Trident, I don't think we can afford it. A tax " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'on banks I think is now unavoidable. Tax credits. We need to look at ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'public sector pensions. These are big decisions we need to take. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 290.0), (728.0, 739.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'David Cameron? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 442.0), (72.0, 83.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'I would like us for once to get politicians together...  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 489.0), (95.0, 106.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"Yeah. I've got the agenda, Mr Clegg. Mr Cameron's response. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 514.0), (130.0, 187.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'I just want to make this... I think people at home watching will find it ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"extraordinary that Gordon Brown is really saying, you've got to go " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'on wasting money to keep the economy going. Why not cut the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"waste and stop the tax rise? It can't be in... How is a 7% pay rise for " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'NHS managers essential for economic growth? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 366.0), (199.0, 210.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"I'm going to have to park it there... " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 319.0), (233.0, 244.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'We made 35 billion of... ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 511.0), (256.0, 325.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"No, I'm going to stop you because we had some of this in the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"previous question and I've still got more questions that I really want " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to take. A lot of information there for people to reflect on. I do want ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to move it on. Our next questioner comes from an army family and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'himself has served in the Territorial Army. Nick Brimson, your ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'question. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 510.0), (337.0, 382.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u'Good evening, guys. British troops seem to be dying unnecessarily ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and far too frequently. In my opinion, they are under-equipped and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'massively underpaid. What assurances can you give the armed ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'forces that things will improve? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 261.0), (394.0, 405.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Mr Clegg? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (429.0, 624.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"You're right, Nick. They are under-equipped and they are underpaid. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"I think there's something seriously wrong when you've got 8,000 " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'bureaucrats in the Ministry of Defence who work on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'communications. When we have too many top brass in some of the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'services - there are, I think, two admirals for every warship. We ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'have 17 brigadiers for every brigade. And we also, of course, have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'this consensus from the Conservative and Labour Parties that we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'should spend \xa3100 million renewing the Cold War nuclear Trident ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'missile system. I say if we change our priorities, we can provide our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'brave servicemen and servicewomen, who do the most astonishing ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'job in the most extraordinarily difficult circumstances, we can give ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"them proper pay. I think it's a scandal that someone who starts in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the army on a junior rank now gets paid \xa36,000 less than someone ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'starting as a firefighter or in the police service. I want them to have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the same pay, and I also want them to have proper body amour, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'proper helicopters, proper vehicles. You can only do that if you cut ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"out spending elsewhere which isn't being well spent. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (636.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Let me say, first of all, my pride and my admiration for the armed ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'forces, and our questioner who was in the Territorial Army, all those ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"who serve our nation, and particularly at this time when we're at war " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"in Afghanistan, we've got to remember and we've got to do our best " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'not just by the armed forces but by their families. And let us ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'remember all those who lost their lives in Afghanistan. The ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"important thing is that we're doing the right thing by our troops. And " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"that's why we've increased the spending on equipment dramatically " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'over these last few years. A thousand new vehicles, new helicopters ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'brought into Afghanistan. We used to spend \xa3600 million on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Afghanistan three or four years ago. It is now 5,000 million this year. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 513.0), (72.0, 118.0)) {}
  [
    u"Now, this... Every time, you know, I've got to write to a family where " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"someone's died, I've got to consider all these issues. I would not " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'send our troops into battle unless I was absolutely sure that they ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"were properly equipped for what they're doing. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (130.0, 313.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"Sorry, I couldn't see Nick in the audience. Can you put your hand " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"up? Ah... Oh, sorry, you're behind the... Same problem, behind the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'camera. First of all, can I thank you for what you do, and I join with ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Gordon in paying tribute to our forces. I've been to Afghanistan in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'each of the last four years, and just the bravery and the incredible ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'courage and determination of what those men and women do just ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"humbles you every time you see it. They're not just brave fighters, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"they are brilliant diplomats in dealing with difficult situations, they're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"incredible athletes, they are brilliant, brilliant people. But I don't think " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we do do enough for them. I know that steps are being taken to try ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and improve the situation. But, frankly, we shouldn't be in the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'situation we are. In the last few months, we had to fight a battle in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'parliament to stop the government cutting the training for the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Territorial Army. I think it's madness when you've got soldiers " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'deployed overseas actually not to invest in your Territorial Army, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"because they're a very, very important part of our armed services. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 514.0), (325.0, 532.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I think it's also what kind of equipment we provide. I was in a factory " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"in my own city where I'm an MP in Sheffield just a few weeks ago. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'There was a great British company there, a manufacturing ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'company, that produces great metal braces with these huge rollers, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'which apparently are sold to the American army. They attach them ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'onto their vehicles, and when the rollers move over mines, the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'mines blow up, but of course, they destroy the rollers and not the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'soldiers. The American army says that those rollers, diesigned, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'manufactured by a great British business in Sheffield, have saved ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"140 lives. Why is it they're not being used by the British army? " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Apparently they don't somehow fit on to the vehicles that our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"soldiers use. So I think it's not only that we've got to make sure that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we don't waste money on bureaucrats in the Ministry of Defence " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and all the rest of it, and instead spend that on equipment for our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'brave servicemen and servicewomen, we should also use the know-' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'how and the manufacturing brilliance expertise in this country to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'provide our brave soldiers with the equipment which saves lives on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the front line. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (544.0, 739.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Every urgent operational requirement that our armed forces have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"asked us for has been met. I've got two big questions I've got to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"answer to the British people for: why are we in Afghanistan? We're " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'in Afghanistan because there is a terror threat and a chain of terror ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that comes from the Afghan-Pakistan border to our country, and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'three-quarters of the terrorist plots that we identify start not in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Britain, start not in Europe, but start in that border area. The second ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"question I've got to answer is how we can get our troops home. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Because that is what we all want to see at the end of the day. We've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'got to build up the Afghan army, build up the police force in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Afghanistan. Our brave troops are helping to train the Afghan army ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and police at the moment, and that's how we will gradually see the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'numbers of Afghan forces rise and our troops come down in number ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"so that our troops can come home. As we do that, we've got to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'ensure that pay continues to rise for our troops, and those people ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'who leave the forces have got to get proper protection - homes, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'health service and of course, the chance of jobs. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 469.0), (751.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"We all want to see those things happen, and I think it's an " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 516.0), (72.0, 256.0)) {}
  [
    u"absolutely vital year we're having in Afghanistan. And you can see, I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'hope, progress being made but difficult, difficult times lie ahead. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'There is something more fundamental we need to do in order to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"answer your question properly. That is we've got to have a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'fundamental defence review of all that we spend and all that we do ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and all the equipment that we have. Because if you think about it, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'over the last decade, since we last did this, we have had 9/11, we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'have had 7/7 in our own country, we have had the wars in Iraq and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Afghanistan, and yet we fundamentally haven't asked again, what " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'should be the shape of our army, our navy, our air force? How can ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we best defend our country? How can we best protect our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'servicemen and women? We need urgently to do that. We make ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"sure if we get involved in these conflicts in the future, we don't have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the situation where we have had troops on the ground without ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'enough helicopters. We all know that happened after 2006 and it ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"really wasn't good enough. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 514.0), (268.0, 359.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'No, what happened after 2006 is that the Taliban changed its ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'tactics. Before they were in a one-to-one confrontation with us face-' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to-face. They couldn't win that armed battle, so they took to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'explosive devices, guerrilla warfare. And we had to respond to that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'as all our allies had to do. We have 1,000 new vehicles in ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Afghanistan as a result of the decisions to get Mastiffs and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Ridgebacks and other vehicles into the frontline. And we've also got " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"more helicopters as a result of what we've done. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (371.0, 509.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I actually agree, strongly agree, and it's something I've been calling " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for for years, that we should have a complete review about whether ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'our military equipment is right for the job that we are asking our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'brave soldiers and brave servicemen and women to do. Because of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'course the world is changing and the threats to this country are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"changing with it. What I simply don't understand is if we hold that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'review, as I think is going to be likely after the general election, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'whoever wins that election, both David Cameron and Gordon Brown ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'want to rule out one of the biggest items of defence expenditure of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
