  ]
TextArea((95.0, 397.0), (72.0, 83.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you very much indeed. Mr Brown? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (107.0, 313.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'To help people live at home, to give them the urgent care needs ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'they have and see them met, for example, by home helps and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"health visitors, so that people who want to stay at home don't have " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to go into institutional care. We've seen a revolution. Large numbers " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of people are living longer, which is a great thing, but people need ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"help in their homes so that they don't have to go into nursing homes " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"or old people's homes. My priorities for the health service are that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we give people personal guarantees that every individual patient will ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'know they will get a cancer specialist seen within two weeks if need ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"it. They'll get a diagnostic test within one week, and the results to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'them. They will also be able to know that their operation will be in 18 ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"weeks if you're any patient in need of an operation. You'll be able to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"see a GP in the evenings and weekends, something which wasn't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"happening. You'll be able to get a free health check-up on the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'National Health Service. I want people to know that public services ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"are personal to people's needs, and that's why we need to give " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"these guarantees to individual patients, and that's what we're going " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to do from now on. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 513.0), (325.0, 520.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'First of all, can I thank you for your incredible service to the NHS. I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'think the NHS is a wonderful, wonderful thing. What it did for my ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'family and for my son, I will never forget. I went from hospital to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'hospital, A&Es in the middle of the night, sleeping in different wards ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'in different places. The dedication, and the vocation and the love ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'you get from people who work in the NHS just, I think, makes me ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"incredibly proud of this country, so thank you for all that you've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'done. I think it is special, the NHS, and we made a special ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'exception of the NHS and said yes, there are going to have to be ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'difficult financial decisions elsewhere, but we think that the NHS ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'budget should grow in real terms, i.e., more than inflation, every ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'year under a Conservative government. My vision is that we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"improve it, we expand it, we develop it, we make sure that it's got " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'more choice and more control for the patient. But we need to do ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'some short-term things too, like make cancer drugs available to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'people to people who need them. There are some tragic cases now ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'of people not getting what they need. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (532.0, 727.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Of course, the easy thing is to say how much we all love and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'depend and rely on the NHS. The difficult question, which I think is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the one you're addressing, is, how do we protect the NHS which we " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'all rely on, maternity services, A&E departments, GP services and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"so on, when money is tight? I think it's a bit like the earlier " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'discussion about equipment for the army. The priorities at the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"moment are all wrong. The last year under this government, they've " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'employed 5,000 more managers in the NHS, yet the maternity ward ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'in the NHS hospital where my third son was born just over a year ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'ago is threatened with closure. This government spent \xa312 billion on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"a computer testimony in the NHS which doesn't work, yet I was in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Burnley the other day, I think Jacqueline was saying you come from ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Burnley. As you know, they've closed the A&E department there. I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'think you now have to travel 25 miles to Blackburn. What is going ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"on? We're closing A&E departments and maternity wards and " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'wasting money on computer systems and bureaucracy. I want to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'turn that on its head so we can protect the NHS we all rely on. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 511.0), (739.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"I've got to say that my equipment to the NHS is that we will give " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'people these personal guarantees: the main source of employment ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 516.0), (72.0, 244.0)) {}
  [
    u"in the NHS is more nurses. We've got 80,000 to 90,000 more " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"nurses across the United Kingdom. We've got 30,000 more doctors. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"We've got the best equipment now in some of our hospitals. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Remember the situation before 1997, when people had to wait two ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"years for operations? It's now a maximum of 18 weeks. Yes, it is our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'priority that we will support the frontline services, health, the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'National Health Service, education and policing. These are the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'frontline services that people depend on. We will make sure that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that finance is there. David says he will support the National Health ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Service, which assumes he will not give the same guarantees to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'education and policing as I asked him earlier this evening. The main ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'point to recognise is this: David will not give you the guarantee that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you'll see a cancer specialist in two weeks, or the guarantee that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you'll have a GP in the evenings and weekends. These are personal " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'guarantees written into the NHS constitution that we will give. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (256.0, 428.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'The point is that today, actually, the number of nurses is going up - ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the number of managers is going up five times faster than the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'number of nurses in our NHS. The government has had 13 years to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"fix these problems, and it hasn't done. Gordon Brown talks about " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"cancer, but what he's not telling you is that there are people in our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'country, there was a case the other day of someone who had to sell ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'their home to get the cancer drugs. And the Prime Minister, the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"government, is about to hit the NHS, Britain's biggest employer, with " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"this National Insurance rise. It's going to take \xa3200 million out of our " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'National Health Service. We say stop that National Insurance rise, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and instead spend the money on a cancer drugs fund, so people ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'can get the drugs they need. Talk about guarantees, but the fact is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for some people, waiting two weeks to see a consultant is too long. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'We need a faster, choice-driven system, but the drugs have got to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"be there when you need them. They're not always right now.  " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 513.0), (440.0, 624.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'This is a phoney debate. This is pretending that somehow there are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'billions and squillions of pounds around that we can continue to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'pour into our NHS. Every man, woman and child in this country ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'spends \xa32,000 on the NHS through our tax system. I want to judge ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the NHS about how it helps me and my family when we're ill, sick " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and in need of NHS care, not just by numbers plucked out of thin ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'air. David Cameron, you simply cannot seriously suggest that we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'should believe that you can cut the deficit immediately as you want, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'then have a whole blizzard of tax breaks, including a great big tax ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'break for double millionaires in the inheritance tax system, and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'provide huge lashings of extra money to the public services. You ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"might be able to do one of those things. You can't do all three. I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"want to say to people, let's be straight with you. We have to find " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'savings in the NHS. I want to see strategic health authorities, which ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'is a layer of bureaucracy, stripped away altogether and use that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'money on the frontline NHS services which are so important to us. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (636.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'The point is, we have made a special exception for the NHS for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'exactly the reason that Mrs Neville gives, which is that there are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'more older people. There are more expensive treatments. There are ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'drugs budgets that are going up, and we say you need that extra ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"money to even keep going with the NHS. That's why we make the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"exception of the NHS and say that's the budget that has to go up. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'What Gordon Brown is not telling you about the situation with ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'cancer, cancer drugs and cancer outcomes is, after all the things ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"he's talked about, all the money that's gone in, our death rate from " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"cancer is actually worse than Bulgaria's. So all that's happened has " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'not actually improved the outcome, which is what matters. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 285.0), (85.0, 96.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (120.0, 188.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'If people get early detection, and that means screening, I had a lady ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"write to me who said that she would not be alive today if we hadn't " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"introduced screening and we hadn't given the chance to see a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'specialist in two weeks. What David is not telling you is that while ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we're using the National Insurance to pay for health, policing and " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"schools, he won't give the guarantee on policing in schools... " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 373.0), (200.0, 211.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Mr Brown, thank you. Mr Cameron? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (235.0, 360.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON:  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'The National Insurance increase which Gordon Brown has said is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"definitely coming in, that will take \xa3200 million out of the NHS. He's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'not replacing that money, so he would have less to spend on cancer ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'drugs. I have a man in my constituency called Clive Stone who had ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'kidney cancer who came to see me with seven others. Tragically, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"two of them have died because they couldn't get the drug Sutent " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that they wanted, that was on the market, that people knew was a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"good drug. That's a scandal in our country today. So stop the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'National Insurance rise, use that money for the cancer drugs and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'help people, so our outcomes can be amongst the best in Europe ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'rather than sadly amongst some of the worst. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 514.0), (373.0, 452.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'All I would appeal for is just a bit of honesty in this debate. People ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"know that money is tight. People know that you can't promise " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"something for nothing. You can't say you're going to fill the deficit " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"tomorrow and you're going to give lots and lots of tax breaks to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'people, inheritance tax breaks for double millionaires, tax breaks for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'one in three hand-picked married couples, and also extra, extra ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"money to the NHS without explaining how you're going to do it. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 276.0), (464.0, 475.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
