  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I say again there's something wrong... " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 374.0), (522.0, 533.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Mr Cameron? Thank you, Mr Clegg. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 512.0), (557.0, 602.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"Nick Clegg is promising a \xa317 billion tax cut. We're saying, stop the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'waste of \xa36 billion to stop the National Insurance rise. I would love ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"to take everyone out of their first \xa310,000 of income tax, Nick. It's a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'beautiful idea, a lovely idea. We cannot afford it. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 360.0), (614.0, 625.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Shall I tell you how we pay for it? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 311.0), (637.0, 648.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Please do! Mr Clegg? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 509.0), (672.0, 751.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u"I'll tell you how we pay for it. We would, for instance, stop the huge " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'unfair loopholes that only benefit the very wealthy at the top of the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'tax system. At the moment, the top 10% of earners in this country ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'get twice as much tax subsidy from all the rest of you when they ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'make contributions to their pension pot than everybody else. We ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'say give everybody tax relief on their pension contributions but ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"make sure they're the same. And use that money... " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 282.0), (72.0, 83.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gordon Brown. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 494.0), (107.0, 118.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'..so no-one pays any income tax on the first \xa310,000 they earn. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 313.0), (130.0, 141.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Thank you. Mr Brown. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 513.0), (164.0, 244.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Where Nick and I are agreed is that to give an inheritance tax cut to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the 3,000 richest estates in the country, of \xa3200,000 each, the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'biggest manifesto promise that the Conservatives made, is totally ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'unfair to the rest of the population of this country. I say to him, we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'will use the National Insurance to pay for health care, to pay for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'policing, and to pay for schools. He will not be able to do that, and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"he's got to tell us the truth about how he will pay for his policies. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (256.0, 348.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"I'm going to stop you. I'm going to stop you there, partly because of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'time, also because, thank you, Mr Brown, people have heard that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'particular exchange as well. I have time to get one more question in. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"That's why I interrupted at that point. I'm grateful for you accepting " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"it. Now, in what will be, as I've just told thm, our final question of this " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"evening, it's also a policy area that's devolved in Scotland, Wales " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and Northern Ireland. Alan Shaw is a train driver from Accrington. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Your question, sir.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 504.0), (360.0, 417.0)) {'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
  [
    u'AUDIENCE MEMBER: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'AUDIENCE'}
    u'Thank you, Alastair. Gentlemen. When are each individual party ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'going to introduce a fairer system to care for the elderly when it is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'required, especially those who have worked and contributed ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"towards the country's economy, without the need for them to sell " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and dispose of their assets? And what are your policies? ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (429.0, 624.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"Thank you, Alan, for asking this question. I think it's an absolutely " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"vital question. I think it's so unfair that today you can have people " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"who have worked hard all their lives, they've saved, they've paid " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"down the mortgage, they've done all the right things, and yet if they " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'go into residential care, they have to spend every penny of that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"money. And maybe the neighbour who didn't work hard, didn't save, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and went about things in a different way, they get the whole thing ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"paid for for free. I think that's just not fair. So we have... As we " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'know, there is a huge budget deficit, a great big hole left by Gordon ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"Brown, so we can't make all care free, I don't think we can afford " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that. What we can do is say to people, if you put aside \xa38,000 on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"turning 65, we can guarantee that you won't have to pay for " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'residential care. That would remove the need to sell your home to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'pay for care. It would mean you could pass your home on to your ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"children rather than have to pay for your care bills. It doesn't solve " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the whole problem, but I think it'd be a good start, a fair start, in " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'rewarding the people who have done the right thing.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (636.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'I think, Alan, this is one of those rare issues where the issue is so ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'big, and the costs are potentially so great, and it affects every ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'family, it affects every individual, that I think this is one of those ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'issues where I would say, it is worth the politicians setting aside ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'their political differences for once and trying to come up with a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"solution everybody can agree with. We've all got different ideas. We " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"have ideas, proposals, that there's a contribution from the individual " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and the state. David Cameron's ideas, which helps some but " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"doesn't help people in their home. Gordon Brown has some ideas " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"which help some of the most needy, but not others. Why don't we " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for once, given this is something which I think is bigger than any ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 517.0), (72.0, 164.0)) {}
  [
    u'other party, actually work together? There are some things, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'however, that I think we can do immediately. I, for instance, would ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'like to use the money that the government has allocated for its ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'latest, I think slightly flawed, proposals, to give respite care to the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'carers who look after loved ones, those who looked after loved ones ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for the greatest amount of time, give them respite for at least a week ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"every year. That's something we can do now. Let's come up with a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'longer term proposal together. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (176.0, 394.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'Elderly people should not have to choose between the home they ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'own and the care they need. We have to devise a better system for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the future. That's why the first stage of it is urgent-needs care. So " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you can stay in your own home, you don't have to go into a nursing " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'home, you get the support you need to stay in your own home free ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"of charge. We're introducing that from April next year. The second " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"stage in the next parliament is to say to people, if you're in an old " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"people's home and you're in that home for more than two years, it " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'will be free for personal and medical care from then onwards. That ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'will take away the worry and anxiety people feel that their own home ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'will have to be sold to meet the costs of residential care. The third ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'stage will be to move to a more comprehensive system where ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'people can be guaranteed that their needs will be met in the long ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'run. I agree with Nick, we want consensus on this, we want to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'proceed in a way that every party, that every part of the country is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"with us. That's why we are consulting the social care groups, setting " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'up a new commission to look at the finding for the future after the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"next parliament, but we're committed to urgent needs being met " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'now. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (406.0, 440.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"It isn't a small problem about people having to sell their homes to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"pay for care. I believe it's 45,000 families every year who have to do " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"that. As I say, I think there's a deep unfairness in the system. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (452.0, 589.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Look, all of us, when we we get older, want to spend as long as ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'possible at home before going into residential care. Anything we can ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'do to help people adapt their homes and live in their homes, and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'also to help the carers, if carers stopped caring in Britain, whether ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for disabled children or elderly people, if they packed up and gave ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'up, that would cost us \xa350 billion as well as the hurt and pain it ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'would cause. So giving carers clearer rights and saying if you care ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for someone, you should get a break. The thing every carer says to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'me more than anything else is, "Give me a break every now and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'again, and I can go on doing what I do". I hope as we try and seek ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"some consensus, let's put the carer absolutely up front and centre. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"They're Britain's unsung heroes. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (601.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Of course, I agree with that. There are about a million carers in this ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'country who care, I think, for 50 hours or more for their loved ones, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'for members of their family who need care. They are the unsung ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'army of heroines and heroes that keep our society together. They ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'desperately need time for themselves, time to go on holiday. Under ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'our plans, what we could do immediately is give those million carers ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'who care for the greatest length of time at least a week off - at least ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'a week off - just to have a breather, spend some time on their own, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'visit friends, go on holiday, have some time to themselves again. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"But as I say, I think we've all got some ideas, but I don't think any of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"us - and you don't hear this from politicians very much - I don't think " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"any of us, if we're really honest with you, have got the perfect " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"solution. That's why I think this is so important. Let's for once put " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'people before politics and come up with a solution that works for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 370.0), (72.0, 83.0)) {}
  [
    u'you and your family in the long run. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (95.0, 244.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'We have tried to do something about respite care. There are six ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"million carers in this country. I've met many of them and talked to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'them about their needs. One need is respite, so that they can have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"a break, as Nick said. We're introducing, and have actually made " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'provision, for more measures for respite care. But the questioner ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'was asking about, also, how he could be sure that he could be less ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"worried about having to go into an old people's home, or what would " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"happen if he got ill later on in his life. That's why the urgent-needs " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"measure we're introducing from April next year is so important. It " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'means that you can stay in your own home, have the help that is ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'available, the equipment, but also the home helps and the health ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'visitors, and at the moment, it is being means-tested. Now, in future, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'it will be free of charge. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (256.0, 428.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u"I think one of the biggest things we must do is, I think it's right to try " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'and forge a consensus, because this is a long-term issue we must ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'deal with, is to try and give the carer and those they care for more ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'power and control and influence over their lives. Form an individual ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'budget for each one. Make sure that if they want to, they can take ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that as a direct payment, they can make decisions about the sort of ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'respite they need. We tried to do this with my son, and when you try ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and get a direct payment system so you're in charge of the money " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and you can try and get some help, it's unbelievably complicated. " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"You've got so set up a separate bank account, you've got to read " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'about four lever-arch files. I found it testing enough. What someone ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"who's recently had to start caring, who's under huge pressure, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"maybe getting ill of what they're doing, to try and get direct " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"payments, let's make it easier. We ought to be trusting people to do " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'this. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (440.0, 555.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u'I think the key is, of course, urgent-needs payments for people so ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that they are sure they can stay in their own home. I agree that we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'need to do more for carers. I want carers to be able to manage their ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"own budgets as well, and that's something we're really working on " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"for the future as well. But we've got to find a solution to this big " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"problem. The big problem is, people don't want to have to make the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'choice between owning their home and getting the care they need. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"That's why in the next parliament, it's important to try with the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'commission to reach a consensus on what the funding will be for the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'future. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (567.0, 658.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'I think everybody will be surprised that the last question of the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'evening should actually have flowed into so much consensus. I think ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'it is one of those issues, a bit like public sector pensions. I also think ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the scale of the public sector deficit is one of those issues where I ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'think if we could introduce a new kind of politics in this country, not ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the old style of politics, we could actually come up with a solution ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'that everybody could agree to, because I think you and your family ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'would benefit from it so much. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (670.0, 762.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u"Gentlemen, it will disappoint you and many people, but we've come " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to the end of our debating time. If I can just explain to you, while you ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"mull over what you've heard already, what happens now is that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'each of them will have one and a half minutes to make their closing ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"statement. The evening began with an opener. You've heard lots of " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'cut-and-thrust about a number of issues, but now each of them has ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'one and a half minutes to attempt to persuade you of their overall ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'position. Mr Clegg, you first. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 517.0), (85.0, 314.0)) {'type': 'CLEGG'}
  [
    u'NICK CLEGG: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CLEGG'}
    u'Well, thanks for starters, for sticking with us for a full 90 minutes. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"What I've tried to show you this evening is that there is an " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'alternative to the two old parties.  I know many of you think that all ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"politicians are just the same.  I hope I've tried to show you that that " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"just isn't true.  Whether it is on the questions from Alan on care, " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Jacqueline on crime, Helen on politics, Joel on schooling, Robert on ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the deficit, I believe we can answer all of those questions.  I believe ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'we can rise to all of those challenges if we say no to the old parties ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and yes to something new and something different.  That's what I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"offer and that's what the Liberal Democrats offer.  So don't let them " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'tell you that the only choice is between two old parties who have ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'been playing pass the parcel with your government for 65 years now ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'- making the same promises, breaking the same promises. Making ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the same old mistakes over and over again.  I think, despite all the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'challenges, all the problems we have, I think we can be really ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'hopeful about the future.  I genuinely believe we can have a better ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'fairer country if we do things differently. So give real change a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'chance. Trust your instincts. Support fairness. Choose something ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'different. And that will give you and your family a better, fairer life.  ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Thank you.   ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 516.0), (326.0, 636.0)) {'type': 'BROWN'}
  [
    u'GORDON BROWN: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'BROWN'}
    u"You know it's been a great opportunity to exchange ideas this " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"evening.  I know we're not up against The X Factor or Britain's Got " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'Talent and I hope people have been able to stay with us in the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"exchange that we've had about the future policies of this country.  I " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'was really struck with a number of questions, but particularly the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'one from Robert about the future of his healthcare trust and about ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"the jobs that may be at risk.  I've got to come to this central problem " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"that we've got at the moment: we've got to make a decision now " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"about how we secure the recovery this year. We've got to make a " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'decision about whether we put funds into the economy or take funds ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"out of the economy.  Now, I'm very clear we mustn't make the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'mistakes of the 1930s or the 1980s when unemployment rose for ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"five years after the official end of the recession.  So we've got to " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'make sure the money is in the economy this year so that the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"recovery is secure. And then we've got to make sure that as we cut " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the deficit, we are fair to our National Health Service, our policing, ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"and fair to our schools.  And that's why the National Insurance rise " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'is necessary, to protect our health service, our schools and our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'police.  I think it was very interesting when David Cameron was ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"asked, he couldn't give a guarantee that we are giving about the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"funding on schools, he couldn't give a guarantee about the funding " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'on policing.  And when it came to the National Health Service, he ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"couldn't give the same personal guarantees that we're giving about " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'cancer specialist care, about seeing a GP at the evenings and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"weekends.  Now these are problems he's got to address in the " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'future.  I look forward to the next debate so we can get all the issues ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'raised, aired about the future of our country.   ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 287.0), (649.0, 660.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'David Cameron. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 515.0), (683.0, 763.0)) {'type': 'CAMERON'}
  [
    u'DAVID CAMERON: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'CAMERON'}
    u'Well I think it has been a great opportunity to have this debate.  And ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"I think one of the things I've heard during this debate is just " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'repeated attempts to try and frighten you about a Conservative ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'government. And I would say, choose hope over fear, because we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'have incredibly exciting and optimistic plans for the future of our ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'country. A great vision where we build a bigger society, where we ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"get our economy moving, where we stop Labour's jobs tax which " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((212.0, 515.0), (72.0, 210.0)) {}
  [
    u"could destroy that economy. I think it's been shown tonight the idea " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'you have to go on wasting money to secure the recovery is simply ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'wrong. You heard a lot about policy tonight. But I think as important ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"as policy is your values.  Let me tell you mine. If you work hard, I'll " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'be behind you; if you want to raise a family, I will support you.  If ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"you're old and you become ill, we will always be there for you. This " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"is an amazing country.  We've done incredible things. I think we can " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'go on and do even more incredible things but we need two things: a ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'government with the right values and also an understanding that ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"we're all in this together and real change comes when we come " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u"together and work together.  That's the sort of the change and that's " FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'the sort of leadership that I would bring to our great country.   ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
TextArea((95.0, 514.0), (222.0, 348.0)) {'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
  [
    u'ALASTAIR STEWART: ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {'grabright': 300, 'type': 'INTERVIEWER'}
    u'Gentlemen, thank you very much indeed for your contributions to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'this, our first debate.  Can I turn to you as well, all of you here with ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'us this evening. Thank you particularly to those who asked the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'questions, and also a heartfelt thanks to those who submitted ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'brilliant questions but for which we did not have time.  Thank you so ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'much.  Our thanks then to Nick Clegg, to Gordon Brown, and to ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'David Cameron. Stay with us now on ITV1 for instant reaction and ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'analysis of the debate on News At Ten.  Including the results of the ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'first opinion poll on who came out on top tonight.  At the end of an ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'historic moment in television and political history, a very good night ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
  [
    u'to you. Good night.  APPLAUSE. ' FontSpec(2 Times 7.0 #000000) {}
  ]
[
    [
        "INTERVIEWER", 
        "Manchester, in the heart of the northwest of England, is tonight host to a British political first. I'm Alastair Stewart. For the first time on British television, live in front of a representative studio audience, we'll be hearing from three men, each hoping to be the leader of the next UK government in the first election debate.  "
    ], 
    [
        "INTERVIEWER", 
        "Good evening, and welcome to the first election debate. Over the past 50 years, there have been numerous attempts to get the leaders of the three big political parties to debate with each other during an election. Tonight, history in the making, as we're joined by the leader of the Liberal Democrats, Nick Clegg, the Conservative party leader, David Cameron, and the leader of the Labour Party, Gordon Brown. This debate will mainly focus on domestic affairs, important issues that affect our everyday lives. If you want to make your own comments and follow the debate online, you can do so by going to ITV.com. In a moment, we'll be taking questions from our studio audience, but first, let's hear a brief opening statement from each of the leaders. We'll start with Nick Clegg. "
    ], 
    [
        "CLEGG", 
        "I believe the way things are is not the way things have to be. You're going to be told tonight by these two that the only choice you can make is between two old parties who've been running things for years. I'm here to persuade you that there is an alternative. I think we have a fantastic opportunity to do things differently for once. If we do things differently, we can create the fair society, the fair country we all want: a fair tax system, better schools, an economy no longer held hostage by greedy bankers, decent, open politics. Those are the changes I believe in. I really wouldn't be standing here tonight if I didn't think they were all possible. So don't let anyone tell you that the only choice is old politics. We can do something new; we can do something different this time. That's what I'm about; that's what the Liberal Democrats offer.  "
    ], 
    [
        "BROWN", 
        "These are no ordinary times, and this is no ordinary election. We've just been going through the biggest global financial crisis in our lives, and we're moving from recession to recovery, and I believe we're moving on a road to prosperity for all. Now, every promise you hear from each of us this evening depends on one thing: a strong economy. And this is the defining year. Get the decisions right now, and we can have secure jobs, we can have standards of living rising, and we can have everybody better off. Get the decisions wrong now, and we could have a double-dip recession. And because we believe in fairness, as we cut the deficit, over these next few years, we will protect your police, your National Health Service, and we will protect your schools. I know what this job involves; I look forward to putting my plan to you this evening. "
    ], 
    [
        "CAMERON", 
        "I think it's great we're having these debates, and I hope they go some way to restore some of the faith and some of the trust into our politics, because we badly need that once again in this country. The expenses saga brought great shame on parliament. I'm extremely sorry for everything that happened. Your politicians, frankly all of us, let you down. Now, there is a big choice at this election: we can go on as we are, or we can say no, Britain can do much better; we can deal with our debts, we can get our economy growing and avoid this jobs tax, and we can build a bigger society. But we can only do this if we recognise we need join together, we need to come together, we need to recognise we're all in this together. Now, not everything Labour has done in the last 13 years has been wrong - they've done some good things and I would keep those, but we need change, and it's that change I want to help to lead. "
    ], 
    [
        "INTERVIEWER", 
        "Gentlemen, thank you very much indeed. Our first question is from Gerard Oliver who is a retired toxicologist from Cheshire. Mr Oliver.  "
    ], 
    [
        "AUDIENCE", 
        "Good evening. What key elements for a fair, workable immigration policy need to be put in place to actually make it work effectively?  "
    ], 
    [
        "INTERVIEWER", 
        " Gordon Brown.  "
    ], 
    [
        "BROWN", 
        "You know, I've heard the concerns around the country. I've been listening to people. I know people feel there are pressures because of immigration. That's why we want to control and manage immigration. And I when I became Prime Minister, I did a number of things. First, I introduced a points system so no unskilled worker from outside the European Union can come to Britain now. I also said that jobs had to be advertised in Jobcentres where there were skills that there were shortages of that we needed people in this country. I then said we're going to look at all the range of occupations where people come from abroad. I talked to a chef the other day who was training. I said in future, when we do it, there'll be no chefs allowed in from outside the European Union. Then I talked to some care assistants - no care assistants come in from outside the European Union. We are a tolerant, we are a diverse country, but the controls on migration that I'm introducing and I will see go further are the right controls, the right policy for Britain. "
    ], 
    [
        "INTERVIEWER", 
        " David Cameron.  "
    ], 
    [
        "CAMERON", 
        "Gerard, what I would say is that immigration is simply too high at the moment. It has been these last ten years, and it does need to come down. I think the pressures that we've put on housing and health and education have been too great. If you look at the...what's happening with immigration, the difference between the amount of people going to live overseas and those coming here, it's been often as high as 200,000. That's equivalent to two million across a decade. It's too much. I want us to bring immigration down so it is in the tens of thousands, not the hundreds of thousands. How would we do that? I think we need to have not just a points system, but also a limit on migration when people are coming from outside the European Union for economic reasons. I also think when new countries join the European Union, that actually we should have transitional controls so they can't all come here at once. It's been too high these last few years, and I would dearly love to get it down to the levels it was in the past so it is no longer an issue in our politics as it wasn't in the past. "
    ], 
    [
        "INTERVIEWER", 
        " Nick Clegg.  "
    ], 
    [
        "CLEGG", 
        "Gerard, you talked about a fair, workable immigration system. That's exactly what I want. What's happened over the last several years is almost precisely the reverse. You have had lots and lots of tough talking about immigration from both Conservative and Labour governments, and complete chaos in the actual administration of the system. It was a Conservative government that removed the exit controls so we knew who was leaving as well as who was coming in. It's what the Labour government followed up on as well. What I think we need to do is, firstly, make sure we restore those exit controls, so we have borders so we know exactly who is coming in but also when they are supposed to leave. The second thing I would do is this. At the moment under the immigration system, if you want to come and work in this country, you have to show two things: firstly, that you've got a sponsor who is sponsoring your arrival in this country, and secondly, that there is a job for you to do. I want to add a third element: that you also only go to a place, to a region, where you are needed. So that we only send immigrants to those places where they can be coped.  "
    ], 
    [
        "INTERVIEWER", 
        "You've heard what each has had to say on immigration. It's now your chance to contest the others' arguments. And you, Gordon Brown, will start.  "
    ], 
    [
